   "source": [
    "# Ascertaining the generalisability of the structure data"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Introduction\n",
    "\n",
    "In this notebook, we set out to ascertain the generalisability of our data and analysis to the broader TCR space.\n",
    "We compared sequence properties of our dataset to a background of TCR sequences sampled from [OTS](https://opig.stats.ox.ac.uk/webapps/ots/ots_paired/) and also look at how the selected structures fit in the overall available TCR structures space."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "import seaborn as sns"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def rmsd(x: np.ndarray) -> float:\n",
    "    '''Compute the RMSD of an array.'''\n",
    "    x_bar = np.mean(x)\n",
    "    n = len(x)\n",
    "    return np.sqrt(np.sum((x - x_bar) ** 2) / n)"
   ]
  },

   "source": [
    "ots_sample_cdrs = ots_sample.filter(regex=r'^cdr\\d_aa_[alpha|beta]', axis=1)\n",
    "cdr_cols = ots_sample_cdrs.columns.tolist()\n",
    "\n",
    "ots_sample_cdrs = pd.concat([ots_sample_cdrs, ots_sample['sample_num']], axis='columns')\n",
    "\n",
    "ots_sample_cdrs = ots_sample_cdrs.melt(id_vars='sample_num',\n",
    "                                       value_vars=cdr_cols,\n",
    "                                       var_name='cdr_type',\n",
    "                                       value_name='sequence')\n",
    "ots_sample_cdrs[['cdr', 'chain_type']] = ots_sample_cdrs['cdr_type'].str.extract('cdr(\\d)_aa_(alpha|beta)')\n",
    "\n",
    "ots_sample_cdrs['length'] = ots_sample_cdrs['sequence'].str.len()\n",
    "\n",
    "ots_sample_cdrs"
   ]
  },

   "source": [
    "ots_sample_cdrs_proptions = (ots_sample_cdrs.groupby(['chain_type', 'cdr', 'sample_num'])\n",

   "source": [
    "ots_sample_cdrs_proptions_agg = (ots_sample_cdrs_proptions.groupby(['chain_type', 'cdr', 'length'])\n",

    "                                                          .fillna(0.0)\n",
    "                                                          .reset_index())\n",
    "ots_sample_cdrs_proptions_agg.columns = ['_'.join(col).rstrip('_').replace('_mean', '')\n",
    "                                         for col in ots_sample_cdrs_proptions_agg.columns]"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",

   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "apo_holo_cdr_length_proportions = (apo_holo_cdr_sequences.groupby(['chain_type', 'cdr'])\n",
    "                                   ['length']\n",
    "                                   .value_counts(normalize=True)\n",
    "                                   * 100)\n",
    "apo_holo_cdr_length_proportions.name = 'percentage'\n",
    "apo_holo_cdr_length_proportions = apo_holo_cdr_length_proportions.reset_index()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 14,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "cdr_length_proportions = ots_sample_cdrs_proptions_agg.merge(apo_holo_cdr_length_proportions,\n",
    "                                                             how='outer',\n",
    "                                                             on=['chain_type', 'cdr', 'length'],\n",
    "                                                             suffixes=['_ots', '_stcrdab']).fillna(0)\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "cdr_length_proportions['difference'] = (cdr_length_proportions['percentage_stcrdab']\n",
    "                                        - cdr_length_proportions['percentage_ots'])"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 15,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "cdr_length_percentages = (cdr_lengths.groupby(['chain_type', 'cdr', 'sample_num', 'source'], dropna=False)\n",
    "                                     ['length']\n",
    "                                     .value_counts(normalize=True)\n",
    "                                     * 100)\n",
    "cdr_length_percentages.name = 'percentage'\n",
    "cdr_length_percentages = cdr_length_percentages.reset_index()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 16,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "for (chain_type, cdr), group in cdr_length_percentages.groupby(['chain_type', 'cdr']):\n",
    "    length_min = group['length'].min()\n",
    "    length_max = group['length'].max()\n",
    "    expected_length_values = set(range(length_min, length_max + 1))\n",
    "\n",
    "    actual_length_values = set(group['length'].unique())\n",
    "    missing_length_values = expected_length_values - actual_length_values\n",
    "    missing_length_values = sorted(list(missing_length_values))\n",
    "\n",
    "    if len(missing_length_values) > 0:\n",
    "        missing_entries = pd.DataFrame({'chain_type': [chain_type for _ in missing_length_values],\n",
    "                                        'cdr': [cdr for _ in missing_length_values],\n",
    "                                        'source': ['OTS' for _ in missing_length_values],\n",
    "                                        'length': missing_length_values,\n",
    "                                        'percentage': [0.0 for _ in missing_length_values]})\n",
    "\n",
    "        cdr_length_percentages = pd.concat([cdr_length_percentages, missing_entries])\n",
    "\n",
    "cdr_length_percentages = cdr_length_percentages.reset_index(drop=True)"
   ]

  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Comparison of amino acide types in loops"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 28,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "AMINO_ACIDS = ['A', 'C', 'D', 'E', 'F', 'G', 'H', 'I', 'K', 'L', 'M', 'N', 'P', 'Q', 'R', 'S', 'T', 'V', 'W', 'Y']\n",
    "\n",
    "def count_amino_acids(residues: pd.Series, normalize = True) -> pd.Series:\n",
    "    counts = {res: 0 for res in AMINO_ACIDS}\n",
    "\n",
    "    for res in residues.tolist():\n",
    "        counts[res] += 1\n",
    "\n",
    "    if normalize:\n",
    "        num_residues = len(residues)\n",
    "        counts = {res: count / num_residues for res, count in counts.items()}\n",
    "\n",
    "    counts = pd.Series(counts)\n",
    "    counts.name = 'count' if not normalize else 'proportion'\n",
    "    counts.index.name = 'residue'\n",
    "\n",
    "    return counts"
   ]
  },
